# Documentation maintenance

Living docs: `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md`, `docs/PIPELINE.md`, `AGENTS.md`, and
app READMEs under `apps/*/`. Use **Mermaid** for all workflow/architecture
diagrams (see `mermaid-docs.mdc`).

Update in the **same commit** as code changes:

- **API routes** → `PIPELINE.md` endpoint table + sequence diagram if flow changed
- **DB schema** (new migration) → ER diagram in `ARCHITECTURE.md` §4
- **BLE / mobile sync** → state machine in `ARCHITECTURE.md` §3, BLE section in `PIPELINE.md`, `apps/mobile/docs/BLE_PROTOCOL.md`
- **Deployment / Docker** → deployment diagram in `ARCHITECTURE.md` §7
- **New packages/apps** → layout tables in README + `ARCHITECTURE.md` §8

Wrong diagrams are worse than none — fix drift even if your change did not cause it.
